---
import GlossaryEntry from '../../layouts/GlossaryEntry.astro';
---
<GlossaryEntry
  category="Arduino / ESP32"
  title="PROGMEM"
  subtitle="Store data in flash, not RAM"
  highlights={[
    'RAM: 320KB - limited, needed at runtime',
    'Flash: 4MB - plenty, read-only during execution',
    'Syntax: const uint8_t data[] PROGMEM = {...}',
    'Read back with: pgm_read_byte(&data[i])',
    'Without PROGMEM: large arrays crash at boot',
  ]}
>
  <svg slot="svg" viewBox="0 0 300 200" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="width:100%;max-width:300px;display:block;margin:auto">
    <rect x="15" y="20" width="90" height="160" rx="6" fill="#1e1e2e" stroke="#cc3333" stroke-width="1.5"/>
    <text x="60" y="42" fill="#e05050" font-size="10" font-family="monospace" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="bold">RAM</text>
    <text x="60" y="55" fill="#888" font-size="8" font-family="monospace" text-anchor="middle">320 KB</text>
    <text x="60" y="153" fill="#e05050" font-size="9" font-family="monospace" text-anchor="middle">FULL</text>
    <text x="150" y="108" fill="#e8a020" font-size="8" font-family="monospace" text-anchor="middle">PROGMEM</text>
    <rect x="195" y="20" width="90" height="160" rx="6" fill="#1e1e2e" stroke="#2ecc71" stroke-width="1.5"/>
    <text x="240" y="42" fill="#2ecc71" font-size="10" font-family="monospace" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="bold">Flash</text>
    <text x="240" y="55" fill="#888" font-size="8" font-family="monospace" text-anchor="middle">4 MB</text>
    <text x="240" y="168" fill="#27ae60" font-size="9" font-family="monospace" text-anchor="middle">safe</text>
  </svg>
  <Fragment slot="desc">
    <p>PROGMEM is a compiler attribute that tells the ESP32 to store a variable in flash memory instead of RAM. The ESP32 has only 320KB of RAM - a 1-second audio clip at 8kHz is already 8KB, and a few clips would overflow it.</p>
    <p>Flash is 4MB and is not used at runtime, so storing audio data there leaves RAM free for the program.</p>
  </Fragment>
</GlossaryEntry>
